This product includes user-creation and lockdown code patterns adapted from
SandVault (https://github.com/webcoyote/sandvault), Copyright (C) 2026
Patrick Wyatt, licensed under the Apache License, Version 2.0.

Specifically adapted:
  - The `dscl . -create` flow for macOS system-user creation, including the
    attribute set (UniqueID, PrimaryGroupID, RealName, NFSHomeDirectory,
    UserShell, IsHidden, password via dscl -passwd).
  - The `dseditgroup -o edit -d <user> -t user staff` lockdown step that
    removes the new daemon user from the default macOS `staff` group.
  - The `dseditgroup -o edit -a <user> -t user <group>` pattern for adding
    the daemon user to its dedicated group.
  - The random-password generation via `openssl rand -base64 32` to make
    the system account unlogin-able.
  - The `IsHidden 1` flag to hide the daemon account from the login window.

These adaptations are clearly marked in the source code with citations to
the upstream commit SHA and inline comments referencing the SandVault project.

